$ Excel Object Model: OLEObject / MSForms / CommandButton

{ create-dynamically.vb

 `create-dynamically.vb` is a simple → development/languages/VBA script that dynamically creates two Active-X (OLE) buttons using the
  → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions[user defined function] `addButton`.
  -
  Its first parameter specifies the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range] that the button should occupy.
  -
  The second parameter specifies the caption of the button.
  -
  The third parameter is the (one line) VBA code to be executed when the button is clicked.

  Additionaly, clicking the button randomly changes the button's color.

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/commandButton/create-dynamically.vb||

}
{ Result

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/commandButton/img/create-dynamically.png||

}
{ create-dynamically.wsf

 `create-dynamically.wsf` is a simple script that creates the Excel workbook and inserts `create-dynamically.vb`. It requires
  the → Microsoft/Office/VBScript-App-Creator and must be invoked on the command line like so:
code {
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cscript_exe[script]  .\create-dynamically.wsf
code }

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/commandButton/create-dynamically.wsf||

}

sa:

  The `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/OLEObject` and the
   `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Button` object in → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model[Excel's object model].

  → development/languages/VBA/Useful-object-libraries/Microsoft-Forms

